oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photo postcard of Lt. Nathan S. Ring
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Lt. Nathan S. Ring is shown in his WWI uniform. Lt. Ring served in several field artillery regiments during the war, but never served overseas. His older brother, Maj. Joseph Ring served in the 308th Eng. Battn. and his younger brother, Pvt. Frank Ring served in Co. A, 117th MG Battn., 30th Div. Frank was killed in action in October 1918. The Ring brothers were from Franklin, Williamson County, Tennessee.
